+## Regression
+
+### Noisy git wrapper stdout does not leak
+
+Some git wrappers write progress to stdout even when passed `--quiet`.
+`antidote-script` must keep that text out of generated plugin scripts while
+still allowing it to surface on stderr as diagnostics.
+
+```zsh
+% function git { echo "NOISY-PROGRESS-STDOUT"; mockgit "$@" }
+% antidote-script --kind zsh https://fakegitsite.com/fakeuser/fakerepo 2>/dev/null | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+fpath+=( "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo" )
+source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/fakeuser/fakerepo/fakerepo.plugin.zsh"
+% # restore mock git for remaining tests
+% function git { mockgit "$@" }
+%
+```
+
